Package com.yardi.shared.QSECOFR

Class EditUserProfileRequest

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.yardi.shared.QSECOFR.EditUserProfileRequest
  • public class EditUserProfileRequest
extends java.lang.Object
    Java representation of the web request to edit the user profile and the response to that request.

    The web request comes in as JSON and gets mapped to this class to make it easier to work with the request. When responding to the request, select fields are mapped to JSON to become the response. Fields annotated @JsonIgnore are not mapped in either the request or the response.

      • birthDate

        private java.util.Date birthDate
        @JsonIgnore Birth date

        This field is not mapped to JSON or from JSON. A GregorianCalendar is constructed from the century, year, month and day components of field dob. birthDate is then set from the GregorianCalendar mills.

      • upHomeMarket

        private short upHomeMarket
        @JsonIgnore Home market

        This field is not mapped to JSON or from JSON. Field homeMarket is parsed to short to set the value for upHomeMarket.

      • passwordExpirationDate

        private java.util.Date passwordExpirationDate
        @JsonIgnore Password expiration date.

        This field is not mapped to JSON or from JSON. The password must be changed on or after this date. A GregorianCalendar is constructed from the century, year, month and day components of field pwdExpDate. passwordExpirationDate is then set from the GregorianCalendar mills.

      • profileDisabledDate

        private java.sql.Timestamp profileDisabledDate
        @JsonIgnore User profile disabled Timestamp.

        This field is not mapped to JSON or from JSON. The date and time when the profile was disabled due to too many invalid password attempts since the last successful login. A GregorianCalendar is constructed using the century, year, month and day components of field disabledDate. The GregorianCalendar time is set to the hour, minute and second components of field disabledTime. Field profileDisabledDate is set from the GregorianCalendar mills.

      • lastLoginDate

        private java.sql.Timestamp lastLoginDate
        @JsonIgnore Date and time of the most recent successful login.

        This field is not mapped to JSON or from JSON. A GregorianCalendar is constructed using the century, year, month and day components of field lastLogin. The GregorianCalendar time is set to the hour, minute and second components of field lastLoginTime. Field lastLoginDate is set from the GregorianCalendar mills.

      • passwordAttempts

        private short passwordAttempts
        @JsonIgnore Number of invalid password attempts since the most recent successful login.

        This field is not mapped to JSON or from JSON. Field pwdAttempts is parsed to short to set the value for passwordAttempts.

        public EditUserProfileRequest​(java.lang.String action,

                              java.lang.String activeYN,
                              java.lang.String pwdExpDate,
                              java.lang.String disabledDate,
                              java.lang.String disabledTime,
                              java.lang.String pwdAttempts,
                              java.lang.String currentToken,
                              java.lang.String lastLogin,
                              java.lang.String lastLoginTime)
        Constructor used when responding to the web request.

        All parms set fields used for presentation purposes. To respond to the web request, values from Full_User_Profile entity are mapped to the parms of this constructor which will set fields of the same name. The fields having the same name as these parms are then mapped to JSON before responding.

        Parameters:
        action - the requested type of edit
        findUser - ID of the user profile to edit
        msgID - message ID
        msgDescription - message description
        firstName - user profile first name
        lastName - user profile last name
        address1 - user profile address line 1
        address2 - user profile address line 2
        city - user profile city
        state - user profile state
        zip - user profile zip
        zip4 - user profile zip4
        phone - user profile phone number
        fax - user profile fax number
        email - user profile email address
        ssn - user profile ssn
        dob - user profile birth date
        homeMarket - user profile home market
        activeYN - indicates whether user profile is active. Y is active. N is inactive
        pwdExpDate - user profile password expiration date. Password must be changed on or after this date.
        disabledDate - date on which the user profile was disabled due to too many invalid password attempts since the most recent successful login
        disabledTime - time when the user profile was disabled due to too many invalid password attempts since the most recent successful login
        pwdAttempts - number of invalid password attempts since the most recent successful login
        currentToken - hashed password
        lastLogin - date of the most recent successful login
        lastLoginTime - time of the most recent successful login

      • setAction

        public void setAction​(java.lang.String action)
        Set the type of edit being requested.

        This setter is called by the JSON mapper com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.ObjectMapper when it mapps the web request.

        Parameters:

        Returns:
        String [] containing the string representation of the date and time components of the given Timestamp. Element zero is the date String. Element one is the time String.

      • toDate

        public java.util.Date toDate​(java.lang.String dateString,
                             java.lang.String timeString,
                             boolean withTime)
        Convert the given Strings to a Date with an optional time component.

        Note that it is unnecessary to return a Timestamp since the mills of the returned date can be used to construct a new Timestamp.

        Parameters:
        dateString - String representation of a date in MM/DD/CCYY format
        timeString - String representation of a time in hh:mm:ss format.
        withTime - boolean that indicates that the returned Date will have a time component.
        Returns:
        Date with an optional time component
